                    <br />
                    <h2 class="intro-text text-center">
                        <strong>Advantages of using Hyperledger Chaincode</strong>
                    </h2>
                    <ul class="list-group">
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            A javascript syntax like language which will already be familiar to most web developers. Chaincode supports
                            many primate data types, looping control, arrays, mappings, and structures.
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">Using the truffle framework, unit testing is supported using both mocha and chai.</li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">Developers have full control over the chaincode regarding which users or groups can execute the code once it is deployed ( ACL lists ).</li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            Hyperledger composer is also available in an on-line sandbox, where you can create and test newly created business objects and chaincode. Developers are
                            not required to install any tools on their local machines. Chaincode and business objects can be exported and then imported as needed.
                        </li>
                    </ul>


                </div>
            </div>
